# Hello, world

Every gemlog needs a first post, and this is mine.

This capsule is brand new — built today, in fact. One small Go server ("capsule") serving the same handful of text files over three doors:

* gemini://owg.fyi — the native experience, best enjoyed in Lagrange
* https://owg.fyi — same content, one small CSS file, zero JavaScript
* a Tor onion service, because why not

The content is plain gemtext (with markdown allowed when I'm converting something over from the big-web blog). Posts land here when I have something worth saying about self-hosting, home labs, tunnels, or whatever else I'm currently over-engineering for fun.

If you want the full-color, screenshot-heavy versions of my write-ups, the regular blog is still the place:

=> https://onewheelgeek.me/ onewheelgeek.me

Otherwise — welcome. Pull up a log by the campfire.

=> /posts/ ← back to the gemlog
